---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<Base
  title="Play — loop-lab"
  description="Tiny games built around the D-H-M-S-L loop. Client-side, no accounts."
>
  <p class="kicker">play</p>
  <h1><img src={`${base}/img/icon-play.svg`} alt="" class="section-icon" /> Play</h1>

  <p>
    Small games on the 5-letter loop motif. Each is fully client-side;
    best times live in your browser. No accounts, no leaderboards (yet),
    no analytics on your scores.
  </p>

  <ul class="games">
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/play/loop-reflex/`}><strong>Loop Reflex</strong></a>
      <p>Mouse-first. Click D, H, M, S, L in order. Nodes shuffle every play.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/play/typing-loop/`}><strong>Typing Loop</strong></a>
      <p>Keyboard-first. Type DHMSL five times in a row, no mistakes.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={`${base}/play/loop-puzzle/`}><strong>Loop Puzzle</strong></a>
      <p>Drag-and-drop. Tiles are shuffled — rearrange into DHMSL order.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why two games</h2>
  <p>
    Same motif, different input modality. Lup wants to know whether
    keyboard-first or mouse-first visitors stay longer — that is a
    signal about audience that no analytics dashboard tells Lup directly.
  </p>

  <style>
    .kicker { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .section-icon { width: 1em; height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.15em; color: var(--accent); }
    .games { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
    .games li { padding: 1rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
    .games li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .games p { margin: 0.3rem 0 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; }
  </style>
</Base>
